<script id="d-js-load-css">
/**
 * There are a few <link> tags with CSS resource in them that are preloaded in the page
 * in each of those there is a "onload" handler which invokes the loadCSS callback
 * defined here.
 * We are monitoring 3 main CSS files - the runtime, the global and the page.
 * When each load we check to see if we can append them all in a batch. If threre
 * is no page css (which may happen on inner pages) then we do not wait for it
 */
(function () {
  let cssLinks = {};
  function loadCssLink(link) {
    link.onload = null;
    link.rel = "stylesheet";
    link.type = "text/css";
  }
  
    function checkCss() {
      const pageCssLink = document.querySelector("[id*='CssLink']");

        if (cssLinks && cssLinks.runtime && cssLinks.global && (!pageCssLink || cssLinks.page)) {
            const storedRuntimeCssLink = cssLinks.runtime;
            const storedPageCssLink = cssLinks.page;
            const storedGlobalCssLink = cssLinks.global;

            storedGlobalCssLink.disabled = true;
            loadCssLink(storedGlobalCssLink);

            if (storedPageCssLink) {
                storedPageCssLink.disabled = true;
                loadCssLink(storedPageCssLink);
            }

            storedRuntimeCssLink.disabled = true;
            loadCssLink(storedRuntimeCssLink);

            requestAnimationFrame(() => {
                setTimeout(() => {
                    storedRuntimeCssLink.disabled = false;
                    storedGlobalCssLink.disabled = false;
                    if (storedPageCssLink) {
                      storedPageCssLink.disabled = false;
                    }
                    cssLinks = null;
                }, 0);
            });
        }
    }
  

  function loadCSS(link) {
    try {
      var urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
      var noCSS = !!urlParams.get("nocss");
      var cssTimeout = urlParams.get("cssTimeout") || 0;

      if (noCSS) {
        return;
      }
      if (link.href.includes("d-css-runtime")) {
        cssLinks.runtime = link;
        checkCss();
      } else if (link.id === "siteGlobalCss") {
        cssLinks.global = link;
        checkCss();
      } 
      
      else if(link.id.includes("CssLink")) {
        cssLinks.page = link;
        checkCss();
      }  
      
      else {
        requestIdleCallback(function () {
          window.setTimeout(function () {
            loadCssLink(link);
          }, parseInt(cssTimeout, 10));
        });
      }
    } catch (e) {
      throw e
    }
  }
  window.loadCSS = window.loadCSS || loadCSS;
})();
</script>

    const defs={};

 <div class="u_1007692926 dmRespRow" style="text-align: center;" id="1007692926"> <div class="dmRespColsWrapper" id="1403355094"> <div class="dmRespCol small-12 medium-12 large-12" id="1208748340"> <span id="1999154304"></span> 
 <div class="dmNewParagraph u_Story" id="Story" style="" data-element-type="paragraph" data-version="5" data-styletopreserve="{" background-image":""}"="" data-anchor="Story"> <h2 class="m-size-25 text-align-center size-36"><span class="m-font-size-25 font-size-36" style="font-weight: 700; font-family: Spartan; display: initial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Welcome to Purgatory Overkill</span></h2> 
</div> <div class="u_1258780446 dmNewParagraph" id="1258780446" style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out; display: block;" data-version="5"><p class="m-size-13 text-align-justify size-18"><span class="m-font-size-13 font-size-18" style="display: initial;">In the year 2075, after many efforts, humanity managed to create its first interdimensional portal. Since then and for the twenty following years many worlds, until then inaccessible, have been visited by exploration teams under the control of the UN. They brought back knowledge and technology. Visited planets have been classed into three categories: Earths, similar to our world in many aspects; peaceful Paradises; and the dangerous Purgatories where violence and evil reign.</span></p><p class="m-size-13 text-align-justify size-18"><span class="m-font-size-13 font-size-18" style="display: initial;">But, like every door, interdimensional portals work both ways and Purgatories inhabitants began to take interest in it. One world known as “Alcion” saw in the portal an occasion to expand its power, not only on Earth, but also on the many planets now connected to our world. UN security team managed to contain the Alcion threat thanks to its tactics and brutal firepower. So much so that it was soon known to the media and the general public as the “OverKill Unit”.</span></p><p class="m-size-13 text-align-justify size-18"><span class="m-font-size-13 font-size-18" style="display: initial;">Less than a month after the victory other purgatory worlds began attacking portals and it’s now up to the OverKill Unit to protect Earths and peaceful paradises.</span></p><p class="m-size-13 text-align-justify size-18"><span class="m-font-size-13 font-size-18" style="display: initial;">As a member of the OverKill Unit you are to be sent to worlds where lifeforms and universal laws are very different from what you have experienced so far. Your only mission is to protect each world’s portal against the assault of its residents until the command center brings you home and deactivates it. If you fail, the command center will fall in the hands of hostile creatures which could then ravage your home, and many more.</span></p></div></div> 
</div> 
</div> 
 <div class="u_1204652141 dmRespRow" id="1204652141"> <div class="dmRespColsWrapper" id="1121881282"> <div class="dmRespCol large-12 medium-12 small-12" id="1219028481"> <div class="dmNewParagraph" data-element-type="paragraph" data-version="5" id="About" data-anchor="About"> <h2 class="m-size-25 text-align-center size-36" style="line-height: initial;"><span class="font-size-36 m-font-size-25" style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Spartan; font-weight: 700;">About Purgatory Overkill</span></h2> 
</div> 
</div> 
</div> 
</div> 
 <div class="u_1749042627 dmRespRow fullBleedChanged fullBleedMode" style="text-align: center;" id="1749042627"> <div class="dmRespColsWrapper" id="1459392360"> <div class="u_1158284275 dmRespCol small-12 large-4 medium-4" id="1158284275"> <div class="u_1475648798 dmDividerWrapper clearfix" data-element-type="dDividerId" data-layout="divider-style-1" data-widget-version="2" id="1475648798"><hr class="dmDivider" style="border-width:2px; border-top-style:solid; color:grey;" id="1388423027"></div> 
 <div class="u_1945301506 dmNewParagraph" data-element-type="paragraph" id="1945301506" style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out;" data-version="5"> <h4 class="text-align-left size-25"><span class="font-size-25" style="font-weight: 400; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); display: initial;">A new shooter and tower-defense VR game</span></h4> 
</div> <div class="u_1065671544 dmNewParagraph" id="1065671544" style="transition: none; display: block;" data-version="5"><p class="text-align-justify size-16" style="line-height: 2;"><span class="font-size-16" style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400;">Purgatory Overkill mixes a shooter and a tower-defense in a VR environnement.</span></p><p class="text-align-justify" style="line-height: 2;"><span style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></span></p><p class="text-align-justify size-16" style="line-height: 2;"><span class="font-size-16" style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400;">Play as a member of the elite group "OverKill Unit" and shoot your way into hordes of enemies, from tiny skeletons to gigantic demons, to protect interdimensional portals which are at the same time you way home and a way for the monsters to invade your world!</span></p><p class="text-align-justify" style="line-height: 2;"><span style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></span></p><p class="text-align-justify size-16" style="line-height: 2;"><span class="font-size-16" style="display: initial; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400;">You can count on your military arsenal to fight, be it loads of different weapons or automatic turrets that you can build around the map to avoid getting overwhelmed. But you will have to protect them as much as they are protecting you. How long can you last?</span></p></div></div>

 <div class="caption-text u_1381233089" id="1381233089"><p class="rteBlock">Full VR gameplay with immersive graphics that mixes FPS gunfights with tower-defense elements. Compatible with HTC Vive and Oculus Rift.</p></div>

 <div class="caption-container u_1084835295" style="display:none" id="1084835295"> <span class="caption-inner" id="1892099251"> <h3 class="caption-title u_1290464777" id="1290464777">Build</h3> 
 <div class="caption-text u_1045678250" id="1045678250"><p class="rteBlock">Build and upgrade turrets to help you fight. Some will help you kill your enemies, some will grant you bonuses, be smart about your building layout and you won’t even have to lift a finger!</p></div>

 <div class="caption-text u_1550291502" id="1550291502"><p class="rteBlock">Use guns to repel enemy assaults. Chose between a selection of 20 weapons (and more to come) across 5 categories (from tiny pistols to huge gatling guns) to be active during the fights.</p></div>

 <div class="caption-text u_1984466995" id="1984466995"><p class="rteBlock">You will have to face different enemies with different behaviors. Some will concentrate on your turrets or your teleporter, other will come for you.</p></div>

 <div class="caption-text u_1111601420" id="1111601420"><p class="rteBlock">Visit multiple locations with different enemies. Each level to come with the early will have a different design with different enemies and sizes.</p></div>

<script id="d-js-load-css">
/**
 * There are a few <link> tags with CSS resource in them that are preloaded in the page
 * in each of those there is a "onload" handler which invokes the loadCSS callback
 * defined here.
 * We are monitoring 3 main CSS files - the runtime, the global and the page.
 * When each load we check to see if we can append them all in a batch. If threre
 * is no page css (which may happen on inner pages) then we do not wait for it
 */
(function () {
  let cssLinks = {};
  function loadCssLink(link) {
    link.onload = null;
    link.rel = "stylesheet";
    link.type = "text/css";
  }
  
    function checkCss() {
      const pageCssLink = document.querySelector("[id*='CssLink']");

        if (cssLinks && cssLinks.runtime && cssLinks.global && (!pageCssLink || cssLinks.page)) {
            const storedRuntimeCssLink = cssLinks.runtime;
            const storedPageCssLink = cssLinks.page;
            const storedGlobalCssLink = cssLinks.global;

            storedGlobalCssLink.disabled = true;
            loadCssLink(storedGlobalCssLink);

            if (storedPageCssLink) {
                storedPageCssLink.disabled = true;
                loadCssLink(storedPageCssLink);
            }

            storedRuntimeCssLink.disabled = true;
            loadCssLink(storedRuntimeCssLink);

            requestAnimationFrame(() => {
                setTimeout(() => {
                    storedRuntimeCssLink.disabled = false;
                    storedGlobalCssLink.disabled = false;
                    if (storedPageCssLink) {
                      storedPageCssLink.disabled = false;
                    }
                    cssLinks = null;
                }, 0);
            });
        }
    }
  

  function loadCSS(link) {
    try {
      var urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
      var noCSS = !!urlParams.get("nocss");
      var cssTimeout = urlParams.get("cssTimeout") || 0;

      if (noCSS) {
        return;
      }
      if (link.href.includes("d-css-runtime")) {
        cssLinks.runtime = link;
        checkCss();
      } else if (link.id === "siteGlobalCss") {
        cssLinks.global = link;
        checkCss();
      } 
      
      else if(link.id.includes("CssLink")) {
        cssLinks.page = link;
        checkCss();
      }  
      
      else {
        requestIdleCallback(function () {
          window.setTimeout(function () {
            loadCssLink(link);
          }, parseInt(cssTimeout, 10));
        });
      }
    } catch (e) {
      throw e
    }
  }
  window.loadCSS = window.loadCSS || loadCSS;
})();

<script>
    dmAPI.loadScript(
        window.rtCommonProps['common.resources.cdn.host'] + '/libs/lozad/1.15.0/lozad.min.js',
        function () {
            dmAPI.runOnReady('lozadInit', function () {
                window.document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(function (img) {
                    img.addEventListener('load', function (event) {
                        var img = event.target;
                        img.style.filter = 'blur(0)';
                        setTimeout(function () {
                            $(img).closest('.imageWidget').addClass('lazyLoaded');
                        }, 250)
                    });
                });
                lozad('.lazy', {
                    threshold: 0.1,
                    loaded: function (element) {
                        if (element.getAttribute('data-background-image')) {
                            element.style.setProperty(
                                'background-image',
                                "url('" + element.getAttribute('data-background-image') + "')",
                                "important"
                            );
                        }
                    }
                }).observe();
            });
        }
    );
</script>
